---
import TTELayout from '~/layouts/TTELayout.astro';

const jsonLd = [
  JSON.stringify({
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'Service',
    name: 'EV Charger Installation',
    description: 'Level 2 EV charger installs with capacity checks, clean wiring, and permit coordination for West Michigan homes and businesses.',
    provider: { '@id': 'https://toptier-electrical.com/#electrician' },
    areaServed: { '@type': 'State', 'name': 'Michigan' },
    serviceType: 'EV Charging Station Installation',
    url: 'https://toptier-electrical.com/ev-chargers',
  }),
  JSON.stringify({
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
    'itemListElement': [
      {'@type': 'ListItem', 'position': 1, 'name': 'Home', 'item': 'https://toptier-electrical.com/'},
      {'@type': 'ListItem', 'position': 2, 'name': 'Services', 'item': 'https://toptier-electrical.com/services'},
      {'@type': 'ListItem', 'position': 3, 'name': 'EV Charger Installation', 'item': 'https://toptier-electrical.com/ev-chargers'},
    ],
  }),
];
---

<TTELayout
  title="EV Charger Installation | West Michigan Electrician"
  description="Level 2 EV charger installs with capacity checks, clean wiring, and permit coordination. Safe, code-compliant charging for your home or business."
  canonical="https://toptier-electrical.com/ev-chargers"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <main id="main-content">
    <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <ol>
        <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
        <li><a href="/services">Services</a></li>
        <li aria-current="page">EV Chargers</li>
      </ol>
    </nav>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <h1>EV Charger Installation</h1>
        <p>Safe, code-compliant EV charger installation for homes and businesses across West Michigan.</p>
        <a href="/booking" class="btn-primary">Schedule Installation</a>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="container">
      <section class="card" style="margin-top: 16px">
        <h3 style="margin-top: 0">Explore by audience</h3>
        <p class="muted" style="margin: 0">
          <a href="/residential-electrician-allegan-mi">Residential electrician hub</a> •
          <a href="/commercial-electrician-allegan-mi">Commercial electrician hub</a>
        </p>
      </section>
    </section>
    <div class="trust-strip">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="trust-badges">
          <span class="badge">&#10004; Licensed &amp; Insured</span>
          <span class="badge">MI License #6220430</span>
          <span class="badge">&#128274; Workmanship Guarantee</span>
          <span class="badge">Owner-Operated</span>
          <span class="badge">Clean, Respectful Jobsite Habits</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <section class="service-detail">
      <div class="container">
        <p>
          Home charging should feel simple: plug in, wake up charged. The important part is making sure the circuit,
          breaker, and electrical panel capacity are planned correctly—because EV charging is a high, continuous load.
        </p>
        <div class="proof-chips">
          <span>Load check included</span>
          <span>Permit coordination</span>
          <span>Inspection-ready install</span>
        </div>
        <h2>What We Install</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Residential Level 2 EV chargers (the most common and practical home option)</li>
          <li>Commercial charging solutions where appropriate (including higher-power systems)</li>
          <li>Dedicated circuits, clean mounting, and tidy finish work</li>
        </ul>
        <h2>What You Can Expect</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Capacity check of your electrical panel and service</li>
          <li>Correct circuit sizing and protection</li>
          <li>Permit/inspection coordination when required</li>
          <li>A clean installation that won't create nuisance trips or unpredictable electrical behavior</li>
        </ul>
        <h2>Plug-In vs Hardwired (Quick Guidance)</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Plug-in chargers can be convenient if you move often, but they require the right receptacle, protection, and
            a clean install.
          </li>
          <li>Hardwired chargers typically look cleaner and are often the simplest long-term solution.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We'll walk you through both and recommend what fits your layout and driving habits.</p>
        <h2>Pricing Factors</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Distance from panel to charging location</li>
          <li>Load calculation and breaker capacity</li>
          <li>Wall finish type and conduit routing needs</li>
          <li>Permit or inspection requirements</li>
        </ul>
        <h2>How We Work</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>Walkthrough — Verify panel capacity and best charger location.</li>
          <li>Plan — Define the circuit, routing, and scope (no surprises).</li>
          <li>Execute — Install the dedicated circuit and mount the EVSE cleanly.</li>
          <li>Verify — Confirm operation, labeling, and safe settings.</li>
        </ol>
        <h2>FAQ</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Do I need a panel upgrade to add a charger?</strong><br />Not always. We check capacity first and
          recommend the simplest code-compliant path.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Do permits matter?</strong><br />Most municipalities require them. We coordinate the process when
          needed.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>How long does installation take?</strong><br />Most installations are completed in a single visit once
          the plan is confirmed.
        </p>
        <h2>Next Step</h2>
        <p>
          Request a quote or schedule an installation walkthrough. You'll get clear scope, clear communication, and a
          charger install you can trust.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="cta-section">
      <h2>Ready to Charge?</h2>
      <p>
        Call us at <a href="tel:+16163347159">(616)&nbsp;334&#8209;7159</a> or email <a
          href="mailto:info@toptier-electrical.com">info@toptier-electrical.com</a
        > to discuss your EV charging needs.
      </p>
      <a href="/booking" class="btn-primary">Schedule Installation</a>
    </section>
  </main>
</TTELayout>
